---
import Section from "../shared/Section.astro";
import Card from "../shared/Card.astro";
---

<Section 
  title="Key Concepts" 
  bgColor="neutral-900" 
  classes="relative"
>
  <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
    <!-- Balance and Imbalance -->
    <Card title="Balance and Imbalance" borderColor="jade">
      <div class="mb-4 h-12 flex items-center">
        <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-10 w-10 text-jade" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.5" d="M3 6l3 1m0 0l-3 9a5.002 5.002 0 006.001 0M6 7l3 9M6 7l6-2m6 2l3-1m-3 1l-3 9a5.002 5.002 0 006.001 0M18 7l3 9m-3-9l-6-2m0-2v2m0 16V5m0 16H9m3 0h3" />
        </svg>
      </div>
      
      <p class="text-neutral-300 mb-4">
        When creators use more AI attention than licensed, or when allocated attention goes unused, the system destabilizes. Anomalies begin to appear – warnings that something isn't right.
      </p>
      
      <p class="text-neutral-400 text-sm">
        "Each imbalance creates a ripple effect, not just in the system but in the psychological state of both creators and AI entities." —<span class="text-jade">Silas Hale</span>
      </p>
    </Card>
    
    <!-- Reconciliation Process -->
    <Card title="Reconciliation Process" borderColor="primary-500">
      <div class="mb-4 h-12 flex items-center">
        <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-10 w-10 text-primary-500" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.5" d="M9 12l2 2 4-4m5.618-4.016A11.955 11.955 0 0112 2.944a11.955 11.955 0 01-8.618 3.04A12.02 12.02 0 003 9c0 5.591 3.824 10.29 9 11.622 5.176-1.332 9-6.03 9-11.622 0-1.042-.133-2.052-.382-3.016z" />
        </svg>
      </div>
      
      <p class="text-neutral-300 mb-4">
        The process of balancing contracted entitlements with actual usage parallels how we might create a more equitable attention economy – one where every voice has a chance to find its audience.
      </p>
      
      <p class="text-neutral-400 text-sm">
        "I don't just fix the numbers. I facilitate a conversation between human creators and AI entities, helping both express their needs." —<span class="text-primary-500">Silas Hale</span>
      </p>
    </Card>
    
    <!-- AI Psychology -->
    <Card title="AI Psychology" borderColor="accent-500">
      <div class="mb-4 h-12 flex items-center">
        <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-10 w-10 text-accent-500" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.5" d="M9.663 17h4.673M12 3v1m6.364 1.636l-.707.707M21 12h-1M4 12H3m3.343-5.657l-.707-.707m2.828 9.9a5 5 0 117.072 0l-.548.547A3.374 3.374 0 0014 18.469V19a2 2 0 11-4 0v-.531c0-.895-.356-1.754-.988-2.386l-.548-.547z" />
        </svg>
      </div>
      
      <p class="text-neutral-300 mb-4">
        The AI entities in Nextla aren't merely tools but psychological beings with their own patterns of thought, emotional responses, and quirks. Their specialties influence their personalities, creating unique archetypes.
      </p>
      
      <p class="text-neutral-400 text-sm">
        "We've moved beyond programming responses. These entities develop their own psychological patterns based on their experiences and specializations." —<span class="text-accent-500">Enrique Lara</span>
      </p>
    </Card>
  </div>
</Section> 